-- Lew Warns Debt-Limit ‘Uncertainty’ Starting to Stress Markets
-- B y   I a n   K a t z
-- 2013-10-10T12:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-10/lew-warns-debt-limit-uncertainty-starting-to-stress-markets.html
U.S. Treasury Secretary Jacob J. Lew
warned Congress that “uncertainty” over the debt limit is
starting to stress financial markets and trying to time an
increase to the last minute “could be very dangerous.” Lew was
speaking in testimony prepared for a hearing before the Senate
Finance Committee today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Katz in Washington at 
